<item>
            <title>[LU-16812] ldiskfs osd_punch() should check new inode size does not exceed maximum size</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16812</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On osd we don&apos;t check for new inode size before ldiskfs_truncate(), we could overflow the block counters in ext4_es_remove_extent().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="75972">LU-16812</key>
            <summary>ldiskfs osd_punch() should check new inode size does not exceed maximum size</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11310&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/statuses/open.png" description="The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.">Open</status>
                    <statusCategory id="2" key="new" colorName="default"/>
                                    <resolution id="-1">Unresolved</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="dongyang">Dongyang Li</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="dongyang">Dongyang Li</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Wed, 10 May 2023 00:12:42 +0000</created>
                <updated>Thu, 29 Jun 2023 22:04:06 +0000</updated>
                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="371888" author="adilger" created="Thu, 11 May 2023 01:45:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems kind of wrong that we allow &lt;b&gt;creating&lt;/b&gt; a file with size=MAX_LFS_FILESIZE but then we cannot open it?  It would probably make more sense that we would return an error for the truncate operation for files larger than &lt;tt&gt;LOV_MAX_STRIPE_COUNT * ocd_maxbytes&lt;/tt&gt; at the client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something like this is already in &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/41365&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/41365&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14384&quot; title=&quot;data &amp;quot;written&amp;quot; to last stripe of very large ldiskfs object can not be &amp;quot;read&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14384&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14384&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: write and read last object stripe&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="371711" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 10 May 2023 00:14:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Li Dongyang &amp;lt;dongyangli@ddn.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/50898&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/50898&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16812&quot; title=&quot;ldiskfs osd_punch() should check new inode size does not exceed maximum size&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16812&quot;&gt;LU-16812&lt;/a&gt; osd-ldiskfs: check inode new size before truncate&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: b68d6ea613477d39ecdadc8d8131554a1a5bf27d&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
